11
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:08,660
Manager.

12
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:10,870
Please, you have to help me out this time.

13
00:01:12,130 --> 00:01:14,040
I'm begging you, please?

14
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,740
My mom just had surgery.

15
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:20,009
If you can just adjust this one dispatch for me,

16
00:01:20,010 --> 00:01:21,880
I'll work straight through without any days off.

17
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:24,149
I'll handle all the fare deposits, too.

18
00:01:24,150 --> 00:01:25,379
You know I'm good with mental math...

19
00:01:25,380 --> 00:01:27,180
Forget it!

20
00:01:27,650 --> 00:01:29,180
I don't need you to handle the fare deposits.

21
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:32,390
We already don't have enough conductors.

22
00:01:33,020 --> 00:01:34,389
Manager, just this once...

23
00:01:34,390 --> 00:01:36,529
Manager, my foot. I told you, the answer is no!

24
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:37,729
Think about it.

25
00:01:37,730 --> 00:01:39,659
If I made an exception for every sob story,

26
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:41,960
how could I possibly run this company?

27
00:01:42,630 --> 00:01:45,829
If you want to leave a hole so bad, why don't you just quit?

28
00:01:45,830 --> 00:01:47,200
Just make a clean break of it.

29
00:01:47,570 --> 00:01:51,710
The only hole I see is the one in your sock.

30
00:01:51,910 --> 00:01:54,339
So who mends that holey sock of yours for you?

31
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:56,379
Your poor old mother has to, right?

32
00:01:56,380 --> 00:01:58,249
Since you still haven't managed to get married.

33
00:01:58,250 --> 00:02:00,119
If you're not going to mend it, then keep your mouth shut.

34
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,519
And it's a mother just like her...

35
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:04,150
who had to be cut open and stitched back up.

36
00:02:04,350 --> 00:02:06,289
And you're just brushing her daughter off like that?

37
00:02:06,290 --> 00:02:07,990
That's just heartless!

38
00:02:08,260 --> 00:02:10,959
We'll cover for Yeong Rye.

39
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,960
So that should work, right?

40
00:02:12,490 --> 00:02:13,630
Guys...

41
00:02:15,430 --> 00:02:19,170
Look at you all, putting on this little show?

42
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:23,740
What an impressive display of friendship!

43
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:25,910
But too bad.

44
00:02:28,210 --> 00:02:30,410
You girls alone aren't enough to cover it.

45
00:02:30,610 --> 00:02:34,150
So, am I going to approve this or am I not?

46
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:38,090
Ms. Koh! Do I approve it, or do I not?

47
00:02:38,290 --> 00:02:41,060
Then I'll cover the shift, too.

48
00:02:44,090 --> 00:02:48,060
With three of us covering, we should be able to manage.

49
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:50,370
Jong Hee.

50
00:02:58,570 --> 00:03:01,440
Aren't you all pushing yourselves too hard for me?

51
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:05,410
It'll be exhausting working without any days off.

52
00:03:05,610 --> 00:03:06,750
Hey, now.

53
00:03:06,950 --> 00:03:08,250
What are friends for?

54
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:11,450
Now, you're starting to hurt my feelings.

55
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:12,650
That's right.

56
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:14,460
To be blunt,

57
00:03:14,660 --> 00:03:16,090
if we were in your shoes,

58
00:03:16,890 --> 00:03:18,990
you'd do the same for us, wouldn't you?

59
00:03:19,590 --> 00:03:20,899
Exactly.

60
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:23,570
That's what friends are for. Right?

61
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:31,140
But how long are those two going to keep this up?

62
00:03:31,340 --> 00:03:32,810
It's making us uncomfortable just watching.

63
00:03:38,450 --> 00:03:40,520
All because of one stupid player.

64
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:44,020
A friendship flimsier than tissue is torn to shreds.

65
00:03:45,150 --> 00:03:46,320
Tell me about it.

66
00:03:47,390 --> 00:03:50,190
They used to be inseparable, for goodness' sake.

67
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,460
I don't get it either.

68
00:03:53,130 --> 00:03:56,330
There are plenty of fish in the sea. Why act like this over a guy?

69
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,190
Here.

70
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:24,530
Could you give this to Seo Jong Hee for me?

71
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:40,439
(Episode 4: One Step Behind)

72
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:44,749
(Episode 4: One Step Behind)

73
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:46,719
(Jeongsin High School)

74
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:50,449
Loser, moron, airhead, simpleton.

75
00:04:50,450 --> 00:04:53,789
- Loser, moron, idiot. - Is that all you've got?

76
00:04:53,790 --> 00:04:54,820
Hit it harder.

77
00:04:55,290 --> 00:04:56,390
Idiot!

78
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,360
Hey.

79
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,699
You know, if I had a time machine?

80
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,970
I'd go straight back to the exhibition match.

81
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:05,999
Then I'd cut Deok Gu off at the pass...

82
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,770
and knock him out with an uppercut.

83
00:05:08,570 --> 00:05:09,670
Then Yeong Rye would be like,

84
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,539
"Oh, my. Sang Cheol."

85
00:05:11,540 --> 00:05:13,410
"How can you be so manly and amazing?"

86
00:05:13,610 --> 00:05:15,610
"I think I've fallen head over heels for you."

87
00:05:15,710 --> 00:05:16,750
That's what she'd say, right?

88
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:21,980
You lunatic.

89
00:05:22,850 --> 00:05:25,090
Right? I'm a lunatic, like you said.

90
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,890
What is wrong with me?

91
00:05:31,930 --> 00:05:33,300
Now that I know it's too late,

92
00:05:34,130 --> 00:05:36,500
I find myself missing her even more.

93
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:40,740
If it's that bad, why don't you visit her in the hospital?

94
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,100
Visit her at the hospital?

95
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,670
Who?

96
00:05:51,710 --> 00:05:53,850
For goodness' sake, what's all the fuss?

97
00:05:54,050 --> 00:05:55,620
I said, just go already.

98
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:59,390
Good grief. You're so stubborn.

99
00:05:59,790 --> 00:06:01,390
You're as stubborn as a mule.

100
00:06:01,460 --> 00:06:03,090
I'm telling you, I'm fine.

101
00:06:03,290 --> 00:06:06,600
My coworkers said they'd cover my shifts, I told you.

102
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,460
In that case,

103
00:06:10,470 --> 00:06:12,030
you should visit our home.

104
00:06:12,430 --> 00:06:14,140
Check on the kids,

105
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:17,940
do the laundry, and make some side dishes, okay?

106
00:06:18,340 --> 00:06:20,740
Yeong Sik can't handle all that by himself.

107
00:06:21,310 --> 00:06:23,710
With all his studies and tutoring, he's already struggling as it is.

108
00:06:24,110 --> 00:06:25,179
Goodness.

109
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:26,180
Mom.

110
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,920
Even in a time like this, all you care about is Yeong Sik?

111
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:31,120
Of course. He's the pillar of this family.

112
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:33,790
Then what does that make me?

113
00:06:33,990 --> 00:06:35,120
You're...

114
00:06:36,860 --> 00:06:38,730
You're my daughter. My eldest daughter.

115
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,800
Right.

116
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:44,930
I'm the eldest daughter.

117
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,800
The one who has to earn money and take care of her siblings.

118
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,639
When my own mother treats me so thoughtlessly,

119
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:54,009
who in the world would ever cherish me? Right?

120
00:06:54,010 --> 00:06:55,580
Good grief, this girl.

121
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,350
Did you wake up on the wrong side of the bed?

122
00:06:59,350 --> 00:07:01,150
Why are you being so prickly?

123
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:02,250
I don't know.

124
00:07:03,550 --> 00:07:05,920
That's just how the words are coming out today.

125
00:07:09,290 --> 00:07:10,730
Look who's here, the pillar of the family.

126
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:14,030
I'm going to go look after the kids, do laundry, and make some food.

127
00:07:14,230 --> 00:07:15,900
So you, Mr. Pillar, can take care of Mom.

128
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,700
And don't just wolf down the canned peaches by yourself.

129
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:20,040
Make sure Mom gets some, too.

130
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:24,510
- What's going on with her? - I don't know.

131
00:07:25,940 --> 00:07:27,880
Maybe something happened at work?

132
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,779
Stomp.

133
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:33,320
- Get clean. - Get clean.

134
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:35,779
- Jong Hee. I'm good at this, right? - Yes? You're the best.

135
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:37,119
- Me too, right? - The best!

136
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:38,820
- Harder! Stomp. - Jong Hee.

137
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:41,119
- Yeong Rye! -Yeong Rye!

138
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,120
You're here?

139
00:07:42,990 --> 00:07:45,260
What are you doing here without telling me?

140
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:47,600
When did you get here?

141
00:07:47,660 --> 00:07:48,760
A little while ago.

142
00:07:50,530 --> 00:07:51,530
Over there.

143
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:55,540
I know you couldn't make it to class yesterday.

144
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,210
You know I don't normally take notes, right?

145
00:07:58,970 --> 00:08:01,240
But I took really detailed notes with the fountain pen you gave me.

146
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:05,810
And don't get on my case if it looks like a bunch of chicken scratch.

147
00:08:06,010 --> 00:08:07,820
I really did my best.

148
00:08:08,650 --> 00:08:11,190
Stomp!

149
00:08:14,860 --> 00:08:17,789
What are you waiting for? We need to feed the kids, right?

150
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:20,499
They've been working really hard, so I bet they're starving.

151
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,359
- Yes. - Right? You're hungry, aren't you?

152
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:23,470
- Yes! - Yes!

153
00:08:23,930 --> 00:08:25,200
All right.

154
00:08:25,670 --> 00:08:26,940
I'll go make some food right away.

155
00:08:52,290 --> 00:08:53,860
I love the flowerbed at your house.

156
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,760
The flowers are so pretty,

157
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,470
and your vegetable garden is great, too.

158
00:09:06,540 --> 00:09:09,380
Your mother's doing okay now, right?

159
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:11,010
Yes.

160
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:12,650
But...

161
00:09:13,150 --> 00:09:16,550
I won't let her leave the hospital until she's fully recovered.

162
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:19,749
I'm worried she'll try to go right back to work.

163
00:09:19,750 --> 00:09:23,190
Yes, that sounds exactly like your mom.

164
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:26,390
I was so shocked when I heard she was going into surgery.

165
00:09:26,590 --> 00:09:27,930
I nearly fainted.

166
00:09:28,530 --> 00:09:30,199
That can't ever happen again.

167
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,200
Yes.

168
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:33,870
Here.

169
00:09:44,450 --> 00:09:46,179
Jong Hee.

170
00:09:46,180 --> 00:09:47,250
Yes?

171
00:09:56,190 --> 00:09:57,260
Here.

172
00:09:58,790 --> 00:09:59,790
What is it?

173
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,100
On the day my mom collapsed,

174
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:09,540
I ran into Han Jae Pil on the street.

175
00:10:09,740 --> 00:10:10,840
Han Jae Pil?

176
00:10:12,340 --> 00:10:14,080
(Han Jae Pil)

177
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:17,950
I was desperately trying to catch a cab,

178
00:10:18,450 --> 00:10:20,580
and he gave me a ride to the hospital...

179
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:22,419
in his family's car.

180
00:10:22,420 --> 00:10:23,520
Really?

181
00:10:24,150 --> 00:10:25,450
That was really nice of him.

182
00:10:30,830 --> 00:10:31,930
He...

183
00:10:32,330 --> 00:10:34,560
asked me to give this to you.

184
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,060
- Me? - Yes.

185
00:10:39,770 --> 00:10:42,200
You know how he invited us to the boxing gym?

186
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,370
I guess he did that for you.

187
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,780
And I had no idea.

188
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:50,110
I totally jumped the gun and got my hopes up.

189
00:10:51,650 --> 00:10:52,650
Really?

190
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:54,820
What a strange guy.

191
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:57,490
I don't know about that.

192
00:10:59,650 --> 00:11:03,160
But anyway, I gave it to you.

193
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:05,290
Mission accomplished!

194
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:07,830
What about you?

195
00:11:08,830 --> 00:11:10,630
I thought you were into him.

196
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:12,370
Me?

197
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:17,439
No, I thought he was the one who was into me.

198
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:20,279
So I decided to give him a chance.

199
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:21,309
You know, something like that.

200
00:11:21,310 --> 00:11:22,980
No, I'm not.

201
00:11:23,180 --> 00:11:25,250
He's not even my type.

202
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:27,880
Really?

203
00:11:50,670 --> 00:11:52,610
Why?

204
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:55,380
You don't like him?

205
00:11:56,140 --> 00:11:57,510
It's not about liking him or not.

206
00:11:58,810 --> 00:12:00,320
I'm not interested in dating.

207
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:02,650
I don't have the energy for it either.

208
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:05,490
Besides,

209
00:12:08,860 --> 00:12:11,230
he knows nothing about me.

210
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:18,570
I'm going to get more snacks.

211
00:12:18,670 --> 00:12:19,830
You want some too, right?

212
00:12:33,850 --> 00:12:35,019
Wait. Really?

213
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:36,850
You just ran into her on the street by chance?

214
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,790
Yes.

215
00:12:39,590 --> 00:12:40,920
That should've been me!

216
00:12:41,460 --> 00:12:43,830
I should've given you a ride, even if I had to borrow a truck.

217
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,160
Maybe I should visit her in the hospital.

218
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:47,760
Go ahead.

219
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:49,929
I don't know if she'll be happy to see you, though.

220
00:12:49,930 --> 00:12:51,500
Hey, come with me!

221
00:12:52,130 --> 00:12:54,170
You're the one with an excuse to go, since you gave her a ride.

222
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:56,570
I may have an excuse...

223
00:12:57,540 --> 00:12:59,840
but no desire to go. Why should...

224
00:13:01,580 --> 00:13:02,739
"Why should..."

225
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:03,810
What?

226
00:13:08,780 --> 00:13:09,780
Let's go.

227
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:12,250
Let's go. I'll come with you.

228
00:13:12,450 --> 00:13:14,060
Really?

229
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:15,860
Gosh. I'm so excited.

230
00:13:17,060 --> 00:13:18,730
Should I get something like flowers or fruit?

231
00:13:18,930 --> 00:13:21,230
I'm getting the hiccups. Look.

232
00:13:26,330 --> 00:13:27,370
Hi.

233
00:13:27,770 --> 00:13:29,040
Hey.

234
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,010
Hi.

235
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:39,180
Well, I heard from Jae Pil and...

236
00:13:39,380 --> 00:13:42,019
If I hadn't heard, that's one thing, but I can't pretend I don't know.

237
00:13:42,020 --> 00:13:43,990
It just didn't feel right, as a friend.

238
00:13:44,290 --> 00:13:47,459
I mean, we're not exactly friends, but we're not exactly strangers.

239
00:13:47,460 --> 00:13:49,820
It's a really hard relationship to define.

240
00:13:51,460 --> 00:13:53,459
What? Did you say something, Jae Pil?

241
00:13:53,460 --> 00:13:56,199
He said you must be sick of the hospital food.

242
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,269
- Right. - Yes.

243
00:13:57,270 --> 00:14:00,200
You see, Sang Cheol's parents run a stall at the market.

244
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:01,799
Right.

245
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,599
A little something in the food business.

246
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:05,570
It's a pretty big operation for a market stall.

247
00:14:05,770 --> 00:14:07,910
They sell pickled vegetables and fermented seafood.

248
00:14:08,110 --> 00:14:09,440
And business is surprisingly good.

249
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,149
Not to brag,

250
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:13,610
but everyone around here says it's the real deal.

251
00:14:14,220 --> 00:14:16,780
Everyone loves their food, right?

252
00:14:21,290 --> 00:14:22,860
Right. This is for you.

253
00:14:23,620 --> 00:14:24,629
Thank you.

254
00:14:24,630 --> 00:14:26,790
- Yes. - I'll enjoy it.

255
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:34,899
How's your mom doing? Is she feeling a lot better?

256
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:36,600
She is, thanks to you.

257
00:14:37,210 --> 00:14:40,270
Actually, she was just asking who the friend was that drove her.

258
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,639
She said to tell you thank you.

259
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:43,080
It was nothing.

260
00:14:43,180 --> 00:14:44,650
Of course. I was happy to do it.

261
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:50,320
Hey.

262
00:14:52,690 --> 00:14:53,790
Can we have a moment?

263
00:14:59,030 --> 00:15:00,030
What?

264
00:15:15,580 --> 00:15:16,640
Well...

265
00:15:17,780 --> 00:15:18,780
Yes?

266
00:15:19,850 --> 00:15:22,450
About that note from the other day...

267
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:25,050
Oh, right.

268
00:15:26,220 --> 00:15:29,390
It got to her, right?

269
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:30,930
What'd she say?

270
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:32,530
Well...

271
00:15:33,730 --> 00:15:35,100
Jong Hee's not really...

272
00:15:35,930 --> 00:15:39,030
in a place to be seeing anyone right now.

273
00:15:39,470 --> 00:15:40,940
Oh, is that right?

274
00:15:42,070 --> 00:15:44,910
Then why did she even come on the group date?

275
00:15:45,310 --> 00:15:47,710
Was she just there for fun?

276
00:15:48,410 --> 00:15:50,480
I mean, that can happen.

277
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:52,180
That can happen, sure.

278
00:15:52,980 --> 00:15:54,879
Sorry for making things awkward for you.

279
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:57,590
I feel bad bothering her now, with her sick mom.

280
00:15:57,790 --> 00:16:00,560
No, don't worry. It's fine, really.

281
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:06,829
(Wonhwa Jaeil Hospital)

282
00:16:06,830 --> 00:16:09,099
Gosh. So much for acting uninterested in the group date.

283
00:16:09,100 --> 00:16:10,499
You were so stoic, playing hard to get.

284
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:11,530
Knock it off.

285
00:16:11,630 --> 00:16:14,540
When did that all happen, you sly cat.

286
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:17,240
I said knock it off. Say one more word.

287
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,480
Come on. When did you fall for her?

288
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:23,210
Was it at the roller rink? When Jong Hee took her jacket off?

289
00:16:24,010 --> 00:16:25,380
Or was it when she was trying to hold you back?

290
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,120
Don't tell me it was love at first sight.

291
00:16:30,450 --> 00:16:32,889
You wouldn't let it go when I was crushing on Yeong Rye.

292
00:16:32,890 --> 00:16:35,019
And here you are, up all night thinking about Jong Hee.

293
00:16:35,020 --> 00:16:36,489
So that's what's been going on!

294
00:16:36,490 --> 00:16:37,959
All right! I'll stop!

295
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:39,259
- Didn't I say knock it off? - I said I'll stop!

296
00:16:39,260 --> 00:16:41,299
Jae Pil! I'll stop!

297
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,999
I'll stop, all right?

298
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,269
What's gotten into you?

299
00:16:44,270 --> 00:16:45,470
Jae Pil.

300
00:16:45,670 --> 00:16:47,139
Tell me whatever you want to eat.

301
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:49,670
To celebrate you getting shot down, I'll pay for everything.

302
00:16:49,870 --> 00:16:52,809
I'm paying, I said. What's wrong?

303
00:16:52,810 --> 00:16:54,140
I said I'm treating!

304
00:17:47,430 --> 00:17:49,400
When did you get here?

305
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,769
You must not be a light sleeper. You can just fall asleep anywhere.

306
00:17:51,770 --> 00:17:52,970
I am a light sleeper.

307
00:17:53,170 --> 00:17:55,240
I often sleep in places like this. I've gotten used to it.

308
00:17:56,070 --> 00:17:58,070
Kids, your brother is here.

309
00:17:59,570 --> 00:18:00,810
What? Yeong Sik.

310
00:18:01,380 --> 00:18:02,680
Yeong Sik.

311
00:18:02,780 --> 00:18:04,179
Did you two have fun and play nicely?

312
00:18:04,180 --> 00:18:05,180
- Yes. - Yes.

313
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:08,380
Yeong Sik. Look at this.

314
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:11,320
Jong Hee drew this for me. She did a great job, right?

315
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:14,359
Gosh. She's not much of an artist, is she?

316
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:15,520
Agreed.

317
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:17,460
You don't have to be good at everything.

318
00:18:18,860 --> 00:18:20,060
Let's go play inside.

319
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:25,100
You haven't eaten yet, right?

320
00:18:25,570 --> 00:18:27,799
Yeong Rye made kimchi stew and side dishes.

321
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,539
- Do you want me to serve you some? - No, it's all right. You should go.

322
00:18:29,540 --> 00:18:30,569
You need to get some rest, too.

323
00:18:30,570 --> 00:18:31,970
It's tough when you don't rest on your day off.

324
00:18:32,070 --> 00:18:34,380
I thought you had tutoring later. Are you leaving the kids all alone?

325
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:37,680
Yeong Mi said it gets even scarier at night.

326
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:38,880
I'll figure it out.

327
00:18:41,580 --> 00:18:43,180
- Thanks for everything. - Gosh.

328
00:18:43,780 --> 00:18:46,220
I'm just trying to do a good deed, so why do I feel kicked out?

329
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:50,320
You just smiled.

330
00:18:51,890 --> 00:18:53,230
So you do know how to smile.

331
00:18:54,660 --> 00:18:56,500
I was starting to think you were allergic to smiling.

332
00:18:57,230 --> 00:18:58,300
Aren't you leaving?

333
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:00,800
- I'm going. - Okay.

334
00:19:05,170 --> 00:19:08,839
- This is totally my style. - Oh, that's pretty.

335
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:09,909
Hey, look at this.

336
00:19:09,910 --> 00:19:12,109
- This is prettier. - I know, right?

337
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:14,450
- But I think this suits you better. - Really?

338
00:19:15,180 --> 00:19:16,180
This one.

339
00:19:32,930 --> 00:19:34,870
This is no fun by myself.

340
00:19:36,970 --> 00:19:38,770
I miss Koh Yeong Rye.

341
00:19:45,210 --> 00:19:50,080
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

342
00:19:51,220 --> 00:19:52,220
Hey.

343
00:19:53,890 --> 00:19:54,990
Isn't that her?

344
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:56,760
Seo Jong Hee?

345
00:19:59,430 --> 00:20:01,999
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

346
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,960
(Jungang Supermarket)

347
00:20:04,070 --> 00:20:05,730
When did he get here?

348
00:20:10,070 --> 00:20:11,710
- Yeong Sik! - Is it good?

349
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:15,010
All right, let's go over this again.

350
00:20:15,310 --> 00:20:18,150
Until I'm back from my tutoring, what are you supposed to do?

351
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:19,980
We wait here quietly.

352
00:20:20,180 --> 00:20:22,050
And we don't move a single step.

353
00:20:22,250 --> 00:20:23,350
That's right.

354
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:25,720
- Yeong Bae, take good care of her. - Okay.

355
00:20:25,820 --> 00:20:28,660
And if you need the bathroom, tell the lady at the market.

356
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:30,560
- I've already spoken to her. - Okay.

357
00:20:31,530 --> 00:20:33,559
When I'm done later, I'll come back and buy you an even better treat.

358
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:35,830
An even better treat? Like jjajangmyeon?

359
00:20:36,160 --> 00:20:37,330
That sounds delicious.

360
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,070
- Oh, Mr. Koh. - Hello.

361
00:20:44,610 --> 00:20:45,710
And who are these two?

362
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:48,880
Your siblings?

363
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:51,250
- Hello. - Oh, hello.

364
00:20:52,080 --> 00:20:54,050
But why are your siblings here?

365
00:20:55,780 --> 00:20:58,049
Oh, my. Don't tell me you're making them wait out here?

366
00:20:58,050 --> 00:21:00,389
Yes, my mother's in the hospital, so I didn't really have a choice.

367
00:21:00,390 --> 00:21:02,390
I see.

368
00:21:02,590 --> 00:21:05,529
Oh, dear. You really shouldn't. In this day and age,

369
00:21:05,530 --> 00:21:07,459
leaving the kids out here all by themselves...

370
00:21:07,460 --> 00:21:09,729
They look like they're my Sae Ri's age.

371
00:21:09,730 --> 00:21:12,100
And she looks even younger than her.

372
00:21:35,690 --> 00:21:36,690
Stop it.

373
00:21:37,590 --> 00:21:39,130
What's wrong?

374
00:21:40,930 --> 00:21:42,030
Goodness.

375
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,670
You two haven't eaten dinner, right?

376
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:52,440
Here you go.

377
00:21:52,940 --> 00:21:54,980
I hope you like omelette rice.

378
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:57,079
It's one of my Sae Ri's favourites to eat.

379
00:21:57,080 --> 00:21:58,309
Do you like it?

380
00:21:58,310 --> 00:22:00,949
- I do. - Good. I'm glad.

381
00:22:00,950 --> 00:22:02,650
Go on, eat up.

382
00:22:02,850 --> 00:22:03,850
Dig in.

383
00:22:52,030 --> 00:22:54,030
Her name is Ju Ju.

384
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:57,870
My dad brought her back for me from a business trip to Paris.

385
00:22:58,070 --> 00:22:59,710
I'm the one who named her Ju Ju.

386
00:23:00,540 --> 00:23:02,810
She's five years old.

387
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:12,390
This is from my dad's business trip to Finland.

388
00:23:13,090 --> 00:23:16,559
That's where Santa Claus and Rudolph live, you know?

389
00:23:16,560 --> 00:23:18,290
Oh, yes.

390
00:23:28,770 --> 00:23:29,770
Here.

391
00:23:31,910 --> 00:23:33,110
Gosh.

392
00:23:33,910 --> 00:23:36,380
It's called a music box.

393
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:38,950
- Do you like it? - Yes.

394
00:23:39,350 --> 00:23:40,550
Then it's yours.

395
00:23:40,750 --> 00:23:41,920
It's my gift to you.

396
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:43,580
- Really? - Yes!

397
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:48,590
She told her she could have it.

398
00:23:50,260 --> 00:23:54,560
I would hide a single rainbow candy so Yeong Mi wouldn't ask for it.

399
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:57,830
With a beautiful smile, just like a princess,

400
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:01,640
she told her she could have this expensive gift.

401
00:24:14,050 --> 00:24:15,850
Finish these by our next session.

402
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:18,150
And mark the ones you get stuck on.

403
00:24:19,550 --> 00:24:20,620
Okay.

404
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:23,289
Don't just mark them without trying first.

405
00:24:23,290 --> 00:24:24,530
I can always tell.

406
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:26,630
Sure.

407
00:24:27,930 --> 00:24:29,130
Yes, sir.

408
00:24:29,830 --> 00:24:32,200
Is something wrong? You seem so out of it.

409
00:24:32,970 --> 00:24:34,370
You couldn't focus the whole time, too.

410
00:24:34,940 --> 00:24:36,940
When have I ever been motivated...

411
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:38,270
to study?

412
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:44,350
Mr. Koh.

413
00:24:44,980 --> 00:24:46,610
Have you ever been shot down before?

414
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:52,520
If shot down means confessing and getting rejected,

415
00:24:53,590 --> 00:24:55,520
then no, not even once.

416
00:24:56,120 --> 00:24:58,360
You know you sound very obnoxious, right?

417
00:24:59,360 --> 00:25:00,530
I know.

418
00:25:04,300 --> 00:25:05,970
I mean, what is it that women...

419
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,969
find attractive in a guy?

420
00:25:08,970 --> 00:25:12,939
Do you have to be smart like you, for starters?

421
00:25:12,940 --> 00:25:16,009
Like all intellectual? And wear shirts like this?

422
00:25:16,010 --> 00:25:17,140
Who is she?

423
00:25:21,180 --> 00:25:22,380
I'm not talking about me.

424
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:26,019
I was just curious, that's all.

425
00:25:26,020 --> 00:25:28,319
Class is over, so you should go. Your siblings are waiting.

426
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:29,890
And I have to get to the gym.

427
00:25:36,130 --> 00:25:38,270
(Giant Boxing Gym)

428
00:25:45,570 --> 00:25:47,540
Hey, Han Jae Pil!

429
00:25:47,910 --> 00:25:49,010
You made it.

430
00:25:49,380 --> 00:25:51,149
Greetings, my senior.

431
00:25:51,150 --> 00:25:52,480
- You made it. - Yes.

432
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:57,650
I've got some juicy information you're going to love.

433
00:25:57,850 --> 00:26:00,490
Guess who I saw earlier when I was on my way to my mom's store?

434
00:26:02,020 --> 00:26:03,120
Who'd you see?

435
00:26:03,220 --> 00:26:04,489
I don't know.

436
00:26:04,490 --> 00:26:07,089
Should I tell you or not?

437
00:26:07,090 --> 00:26:09,559
Should I tell you or not?

438
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:11,429
Don't. I don't care. Stop.

439
00:26:11,430 --> 00:26:13,030
You're going to regret this. Seriously.

440
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:18,570
I saw Seo Jong Hee earlier!

441
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:26,350
Who's that?

442
00:26:27,350 --> 00:26:29,279
Am I supposed to know her? I've never heard that name before.

443
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:31,750
Is this a pride of a man or something?

444
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:34,219
Well...

445
00:26:34,220 --> 00:26:37,730
She went to Vivaldi Music Cafe, where we had that group date.

446
00:26:38,230 --> 00:26:40,890
Seeing as she was going in alone, she must be a regular.

447
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:47,330
You don't need to try ten times, but you can at least try once.

448
00:26:47,570 --> 00:26:49,570
No? Are you giving up? Just like that?

449
00:26:50,540 --> 00:26:51,640
You're giving up?

450
00:26:52,310 --> 00:26:53,409
Why is there so much dust on this? Hold that.

451
00:26:53,410 --> 00:26:54,440
What?

452
00:26:56,810 --> 00:26:57,810
I'm going to go change.

453
00:26:58,480 --> 00:27:00,810
Are you giving up?

454
00:27:01,220 --> 00:27:02,250
Fine.

455
00:27:05,950 --> 00:27:10,290
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

456
00:27:24,270 --> 00:27:30,080
(Vivaldi Music Cafe, 2nd Floor)

457
00:27:57,140 --> 00:27:58,440
Darn it.

458
00:27:59,510 --> 00:28:02,280
It held up for so long, but it finally gave out.

459
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:08,520
What am I going to do?

460
00:28:20,860 --> 00:28:22,000
Come on.

461
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:24,030
What are you going to do about yours, then?

462
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:26,100
Me?

463
00:28:33,540 --> 00:28:35,040
I can stay like this.

464
00:28:36,440 --> 00:28:38,380
Then give that to me.

465
00:28:38,580 --> 00:28:40,749
No, I'm the one with the broken slippers.

466
00:28:40,750 --> 00:28:42,220
Just wear it.

467
00:28:42,420 --> 00:28:44,690
You came out to go to the supermarket, right?

468
00:28:45,550 --> 00:28:47,750
I can just go back inside like this.

469
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:50,360
No, it's fine. That would look ridiculous.

470
00:28:52,030 --> 00:28:53,560
You've got an image to maintain.

471
00:29:04,270 --> 00:29:05,470
You wench.

472
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:08,740
I'm sorry, Hae Ja.

473
00:29:10,010 --> 00:29:12,550
I don't know what came over me.

474
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:17,920
No, I'm the one who's sorry.

475
00:29:19,290 --> 00:29:22,420
Your hair is already so thin, and I went and pulled it.

476
00:29:24,190 --> 00:29:26,959
Without you, I have no one to hang out with...

477
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,860
and no one to talk to.

478
00:29:30,460 --> 00:29:31,999
You can have Driver Kim.

479
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:34,799
No, you have him. He's a much better match for you.

480
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:37,099
No, I insist. You take him.

481
00:29:37,100 --> 00:29:39,809
No, you have him.

482
00:29:39,810 --> 00:29:43,079
No, I'm letting you have him. Driver Kim is all yours.

483
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:45,449
Hae Ja.

484
00:29:45,450 --> 00:29:47,579
- You take him. - No, you take Driver Kim.

485
00:29:47,580 --> 00:29:50,780
It's you! You're a much better match for him.

486
00:29:53,890 --> 00:29:57,360
This substitute gig is no joke.

487
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:59,030
Oh, my. This is tough.

488
00:29:59,230 --> 00:30:01,400
I couldn't do all this even if there were two of me.

489
00:30:02,500 --> 00:30:03,600
Oh, my gosh.

490
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:09,270
Are you filling in for Ms. Koh today, Ms. Choi?

491
00:30:09,940 --> 00:30:11,940
- Yes. - That explains it.

492
00:30:12,340 --> 00:30:14,170
I had a dream last night.

493
00:30:15,980 --> 00:30:17,210
You know, Ms. Choi.

494
00:30:19,980 --> 00:30:21,550
Looking at you up close,

495
00:30:21,980 --> 00:30:23,520
your eyes are so clear.

496
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:26,750
Like the ocean shimmering in the moonlight,

497
00:30:27,150 --> 00:30:28,360
they just sparkle.

498
00:30:31,590 --> 00:30:33,029
Hae Ja, by any chance,

499
00:30:33,030 --> 00:30:35,200
have you ever heard of the word "yoonseul?"

500
00:30:37,030 --> 00:30:38,170
Spare me the poetry.

501
00:30:39,130 --> 00:30:41,839
What's with the buttery voice?

502
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:44,910
Let's get going. I'm crazy busy today.

503
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:50,880
All clear.

504
00:30:52,150 --> 00:30:53,950
Right, we should go.

505
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:56,150
Let's go.

506
00:31:12,900 --> 00:31:13,900
Get in.

507
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:20,440
What's with the car? I thought you only cycled.

508
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:22,880
It's my mom's. She was junking it, so I took it.

509
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:28,050
By the way, how's your mom doing?

510
00:31:28,250 --> 00:31:29,620
I've been meaning to go see her.

511
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:32,320
It's fine. It's a six-bed ward, so there's no room anyway.

512
00:31:33,350 --> 00:31:35,460
Are the hospital bills sorted out?

513
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:37,819
Yes, I explained my situation to the family I tutor for...

514
00:31:37,820 --> 00:31:39,560
and they gave me a three-month advance on my pay.

515
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:40,860
That's a relief.

516
00:31:41,930 --> 00:31:43,559
So, are you heading to the hospital now?

517
00:31:43,560 --> 00:31:47,000
No, I was at the hospital overnight, so Yeong Rye is there today.

518
00:31:47,830 --> 00:31:49,570
I need to go home and see the kids.

519
00:31:51,070 --> 00:31:52,170
Really?

520
00:32:01,210 --> 00:32:02,579
- Get out. - What?

521
00:32:02,580 --> 00:32:04,579
Take the bus. Something just came up.

522
00:32:04,580 --> 00:32:05,690
Hurry up and get out.

523
00:32:07,690 --> 00:32:08,790
There you go.

524
00:32:12,130 --> 00:32:13,230
Okay.

525
00:32:20,800 --> 00:32:23,100
What's with this guy? First he says get in, then get out.

526
00:32:23,970 --> 00:32:26,040
Seriously, what an odd guy.

527
00:32:29,580 --> 00:32:30,580
Catch me!

528
00:32:31,550 --> 00:32:33,309
Don't let it get away.

529
00:32:33,310 --> 00:32:34,580
Out of the way!

530
00:32:39,390 --> 00:32:41,390
- Grab him! - Let go of me!

531
00:32:41,790 --> 00:32:42,859
Oh, my.

532
00:32:42,860 --> 00:32:47,530
Seeing those boys reminds me of my little brothers back home.

533
00:32:48,730 --> 00:32:50,559
I miss my siblings.

534
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:52,499
Alright. Who's the best kicker here?

535
00:32:52,500 --> 00:32:54,400
- He is! - Okay. Show me what you've got.

