811
00:53:49,990 --> 00:53:51,690
And it's not even your birthday?

812
00:54:01,000 --> 00:54:02,429
If I'd known sooner,

813
00:54:02,430 --> 00:54:04,600
I would've been getting a gift, not buying one.

814
00:54:10,410 --> 00:54:11,680
Well, one thing's for sure.

815
00:54:14,250 --> 00:54:16,550
Of everyone I know, you're...

816
00:54:21,050 --> 00:54:22,860
You're the richest kid.

817
00:54:25,090 --> 00:54:26,289
Gosh.

818
00:54:26,290 --> 00:54:27,360
Rich.

819
00:54:27,560 --> 00:54:28,730
Right. Okay.

820
00:54:29,030 --> 00:54:30,760
I guess I'm rich,

821
00:54:31,260 --> 00:54:34,900
but my father is the one with the money, not me.

822
00:54:35,100 --> 00:54:36,800
But it'll all be yours eventually, right?

823
00:54:37,540 --> 00:54:38,540
So...

824
00:54:39,570 --> 00:54:41,470
Why were you trying so desperately to hide?

825
00:54:42,110 --> 00:54:45,580
What if you ran into him? Would he beat you up or something?

826
00:54:52,920 --> 00:54:56,620
So even a department store CEO beats his own son.

827
00:54:59,790 --> 00:55:00,890
Well...

828
00:55:01,890 --> 00:55:03,000
That's a new one.

829
00:55:06,330 --> 00:55:09,469
He's always had a temper,

830
00:55:09,470 --> 00:55:11,970
but he wasn't always this violent.

831
00:55:13,510 --> 00:55:15,610
Not until my mom passed away.

832
00:55:17,110 --> 00:55:18,610
His self-control has been...

833
00:55:23,480 --> 00:55:25,749
You know...

834
00:55:25,750 --> 00:55:28,320
Your typical sob story.

835
00:55:30,820 --> 00:55:33,330
I mean, I'm used to it by now, so I'm fine.

836
00:55:34,660 --> 00:55:37,200
But when you were there with me,

837
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:39,770
it was just a little...

838
00:55:50,710 --> 00:55:52,080
You're not okay either, though.

839
00:55:56,320 --> 00:55:57,880
You don't have to act so tough.

840
00:56:01,720 --> 00:56:04,460
If you always pretend you're fine, you'll just fall apart all at once.

841
00:56:07,190 --> 00:56:08,960
It's better to admit when you're hurting.

842
00:56:10,700 --> 00:56:11,800
Yes.

843
00:56:17,540 --> 00:56:18,840
How do you know that so well?

844
00:56:19,640 --> 00:56:20,870
Because I've been there.

845
00:56:22,540 --> 00:56:24,880
Acted tough, and then just...

846
00:56:59,340 --> 00:57:00,350
Call me sometime.

847
00:57:02,680 --> 00:57:05,050
We could go to the library this weekend or something.

848
00:57:08,590 --> 00:57:11,160
You already gave me your number, and I shot you down.

849
00:57:11,360 --> 00:57:12,360
I know.

850
00:57:14,230 --> 00:57:15,760
Since I've already been shot down once,

851
00:57:16,600 --> 00:57:18,300
I figure a second time will be less of a shock.

852
00:57:25,770 --> 00:57:26,770
I...

853
00:57:37,050 --> 00:57:38,050
I...

854
00:57:41,420 --> 00:57:42,720
I want to be with you.

855
00:58:07,080 --> 00:58:10,780
(Wonhwa Jaeil Hospital)

856
00:58:11,480 --> 00:58:13,320
- Here you go. - Gosh. Thank you.

857
00:58:13,520 --> 00:58:16,190
- I hope that was enough. - Not at all.

858
00:58:16,690 --> 00:58:18,159
- Thank you. - You take care now.

859
00:58:18,160 --> 00:58:19,160
Okay.

860
00:59:04,640 --> 00:59:06,570
- Good grief. - Oh, my gosh.

861
00:59:07,310 --> 00:59:09,980
Are your eyes just for decoration? How could you possibly miss this?

862
00:59:11,080 --> 00:59:12,180
You startled me.

863
00:59:12,810 --> 00:59:14,079
You're still up?

864
00:59:14,080 --> 00:59:15,250
Here.

865
00:59:16,080 --> 00:59:18,050
Slather it on every time you wash your hands.

866
00:59:19,350 --> 00:59:22,990
It's that hand cream all the young people are using.

867
00:59:23,990 --> 00:59:25,060
Did you...

868
00:59:25,260 --> 00:59:29,159
buy this for me, Mom?

869
00:59:29,160 --> 00:59:32,230
Of course I did. Did you think it fell from the sky?

870
00:59:32,860 --> 00:59:35,070
Your youth is more precious than gold.

871
00:59:35,370 --> 00:59:37,940
You need to start using this thing while you're still young.

872
00:59:38,170 --> 00:59:41,210
Otherwise, your hands will end up a wrinkly mess like your mother's.

873
00:59:43,110 --> 00:59:45,740
Gosh. What's gotten into you, buying something like this?

874
00:59:51,680 --> 00:59:52,880
It smells nice.

875
00:59:53,350 --> 00:59:55,689
Goodness. Don't be stingy with it.

876
00:59:55,690 --> 00:59:57,759
- I'll buy you more when you're out. - It feels like a waste, Mom.

877
00:59:57,760 --> 00:59:59,730
What's there to waste? I said I'll buy you more.

878
01:00:01,360 --> 01:00:02,360
It feels so soft.

879
01:00:03,100 --> 01:00:04,360
- Do you like it? - Yes.

880
01:00:06,730 --> 01:00:07,969
Let's put some on you too, Mom.

881
01:00:07,970 --> 01:00:09,569
- No, I'm okay. - Come on, let me.

882
01:00:09,570 --> 01:00:10,770
I'm too old for this.

883
01:00:23,480 --> 01:00:24,580
Yeong Mi.

884
01:00:25,420 --> 01:00:26,420
Yes?

885
01:00:26,421 --> 01:00:28,620
Do you think my face looks any lighter?

886
01:00:30,620 --> 01:00:31,959
No, it's the same.

887
01:00:31,960 --> 01:00:32,960
Dark.

888
01:00:34,790 --> 01:00:35,989
- Yeong Bae. - What?

889
01:00:35,990 --> 01:00:38,630
That omelette rice was so good, right?

890
01:00:39,430 --> 01:00:41,929
It was so yellow and fluffy.

891
01:00:41,930 --> 01:00:43,030
It really was.

892
01:00:43,240 --> 01:00:44,739
And there was meat inside, right?

893
01:00:44,740 --> 01:00:45,740
Yes, there was.

894
01:00:45,741 --> 01:00:47,269
Don't you want to have it again?

895
01:00:47,270 --> 01:00:48,340
I do.

896
01:00:50,110 --> 01:00:53,080
Sae Ri said we could come over again.

897
01:01:02,290 --> 01:01:05,520
Oh, my. What brings you two here?

898
01:01:05,620 --> 01:01:07,160
- Hello. - Hello.

899
01:01:07,260 --> 01:01:09,589
Sae Ri invited us to come over again.

900
01:01:09,590 --> 01:01:10,700
I see.

901
01:01:11,260 --> 01:01:12,600
But what's this?

902
01:01:12,800 --> 01:01:14,999
Mom said when you visit someone's house,

903
01:01:15,000 --> 01:01:17,670
you shouldn't show up empty-handed.

904
01:01:18,000 --> 01:01:19,070
Okay.

905
01:01:19,270 --> 01:01:20,770
- This is for you. - Okay.

906
01:01:21,210 --> 01:01:22,410
Oh, dear.

907
01:01:22,670 --> 01:01:25,310
All right. Take your shoes off and come on in.

908
01:01:25,510 --> 01:01:27,009
Yeong Bae! Yeong Mi!

909
01:01:27,010 --> 01:01:28,110
Sae Ri!

910
01:01:28,410 --> 01:01:29,980
Hi.

911
01:01:32,980 --> 01:01:34,950
It's the pumpkin from Cinderella!

912
01:01:35,550 --> 01:01:36,660
Yes, it is.

913
01:01:44,630 --> 01:01:46,569
You said you saw her, you punk.

914
01:01:46,570 --> 01:01:48,399
When and where did you see her, you punk?

915
01:01:48,400 --> 01:01:50,400
I did see her at Yeonpung Intersection,

916
01:01:50,700 --> 01:01:52,370
but I was pretty wasted myself.

917
01:01:53,000 --> 01:01:54,639
So I didn't get the bus number.

918
01:01:54,640 --> 01:01:55,809
You punk.

919
01:01:55,810 --> 01:01:58,010
I wasn't sure at first because of the conductor's uniform.

920
01:01:58,710 --> 01:02:01,950
But I'm sure of it. It was definitely your sister.

921
01:02:05,150 --> 01:02:06,220
"A conductor's uniform?"

922
01:02:07,990 --> 01:02:09,690
That wench is working as a bus conductor?

923
01:02:51,630 --> 01:02:53,330
Like you could've gone far.

924
01:03:28,630 --> 01:03:31,400
- Yeong Rye! - Hey!

925
01:03:31,770 --> 01:03:33,410
Hey!

926
01:03:36,440 --> 01:03:40,509
My goodness. It's been a few days, but it feels like ages.

927
01:03:40,510 --> 01:03:42,809
I almost forgot what you look like.

928
01:03:42,810 --> 01:03:43,980
Have you been well?

929
01:03:44,450 --> 01:03:46,220
I made things hard on all of you, didn't I?

930
01:03:47,150 --> 01:03:48,690
Hey, Koh Yeong Rye.

931
01:03:49,190 --> 01:03:50,420
It's been a while.

932
01:03:58,030 --> 01:03:59,130
Ta-da!

933
01:04:01,270 --> 01:04:02,470
Looks delicious.

934
01:04:04,540 --> 01:04:06,600
Let me get that for you. Hang on.

935
01:04:09,010 --> 01:04:10,340
Here, eat up.

936
01:04:15,210 --> 01:04:17,180
Anyone would think you're the patient.

937
01:04:17,950 --> 01:04:19,420
You've lost more weight.

938
01:04:21,020 --> 01:04:22,950
I've been trying to eat properly.

939
01:04:24,160 --> 01:04:25,959
Finish this and have some more. I'll make another bowl.

940
01:04:25,960 --> 01:04:26,960
Okay.

941
01:04:29,790 --> 01:04:31,660
Here, for dessert.

942
01:04:32,230 --> 01:04:33,230
Thank you.

943
01:04:40,370 --> 01:04:42,140
I ran into Han Jae Pil yesterday.

944
01:04:45,180 --> 01:04:47,350
I guess he somehow found out that Vivaldi is my usual spot.

945
01:04:48,680 --> 01:04:49,850
He was waiting for me.

946
01:04:52,950 --> 01:04:54,690
It was his birthday, so we ate.

947
01:04:54,790 --> 01:04:56,550
Then we went gift shopping.

948
01:04:57,360 --> 01:04:59,160
You know Dongin Department Store, right?

949
01:04:59,590 --> 01:05:00,960
It turns out his family owns it.

950
01:05:01,830 --> 01:05:03,630
He saw his dad and tried to hide from him.

951
01:05:04,560 --> 01:05:06,530
I think his father is kind of abusive.

952
01:05:06,730 --> 01:05:08,070
And his mother passed away.

953
01:05:09,730 --> 01:05:12,170
I guess money really can't buy happiness.

954
01:05:15,240 --> 01:05:16,240
Right.

955
01:05:16,780 --> 01:05:18,439
Then he gave me his number...

956
01:05:18,440 --> 01:05:20,050
and asked me to go to the library with him on the weekend.

957
01:05:29,350 --> 01:05:30,360
And?

958
01:05:32,360 --> 01:05:33,490
What about you?

959
01:05:34,190 --> 01:05:35,190
What?

960
01:05:35,930 --> 01:05:37,100
Are you still...

961
01:05:38,060 --> 01:05:39,730
not interested in him?

962
01:05:41,270 --> 01:05:42,270
Not at all?

963
01:05:42,970 --> 01:05:44,470
I don't know.

964
01:05:47,410 --> 01:05:48,610
There's something about him.

965
01:05:50,740 --> 01:05:52,940
On one hand, it seems like he has everything,

966
01:05:53,810 --> 01:05:55,550
but on the other, it's like he has nothing.

967
01:05:56,050 --> 01:05:57,380
He seems lonely.

968
01:06:00,590 --> 01:06:02,720
He does get on my mind, strangely enough.

969
01:06:09,230 --> 01:06:11,600
So why not give him a chance?

970
01:06:11,800 --> 01:06:13,730
A guy who asks me to the library on a date?

971
01:06:14,400 --> 01:06:15,970
No way. That's so lame.

972
01:06:24,640 --> 01:06:26,640
The fact that he doesn't really know who I am,

973
01:06:27,910 --> 01:06:29,880
and the fact that I'm not being honest with him...

974
01:06:31,250 --> 01:06:32,550
I don't like either one.

975
01:06:40,330 --> 01:06:41,630
Don't you think it's because...

976
01:06:42,490 --> 01:06:44,560
you're starting to have feelings for him?

977
01:06:46,030 --> 01:06:48,470
Otherwise, you wouldn't be so upset about it.

978
01:06:51,100 --> 01:06:52,270
Is that right?

979
01:06:58,940 --> 01:07:00,810
I don't even know how I feel.

980
01:07:03,680 --> 01:07:05,150
But there's one thing I know for sure.

981
01:07:06,450 --> 01:07:08,490
I think I have to see him one more time.

982
01:07:09,790 --> 01:07:11,920
I should probably start by being honest.

983
01:07:12,790 --> 01:07:15,290
That I'm not a student, and I'm a bus conductor.

984
01:07:17,230 --> 01:07:19,530
And I'll just figure out the rest after that.

985
01:07:20,470 --> 01:07:23,330
I mean, we'll either see each other or we won't, right?

986
01:07:27,740 --> 01:07:28,840
Oh, right.

987
01:07:29,540 --> 01:07:31,310
I have a full shift that day.

988
01:07:33,240 --> 01:07:35,110
So I didn't even have time anyway.

989
01:07:45,760 --> 01:07:48,190
I'll cover your shift.

990
01:07:52,330 --> 01:07:54,200
You covered for me before.

991
01:07:54,930 --> 01:07:56,400
- Really? - Yes.

992
01:07:58,270 --> 01:07:59,570
You'd really do that?

993
01:08:00,270 --> 01:08:01,270
Yes.

994
01:08:07,580 --> 01:08:08,580
Okay.

995
01:08:10,250 --> 01:08:11,250
All right, then.

996
01:08:13,350 --> 01:08:15,090
I'm going to go make the call.

997
01:08:15,290 --> 01:08:17,289
You finish this up, and just tidy up a little.

998
01:08:17,290 --> 01:08:18,290
Okay.

999
01:08:51,420 --> 01:08:53,290
Yes, hello?

1000
01:08:58,830 --> 01:09:00,000
Hello?

1001
01:09:06,400 --> 01:09:07,470
Hello?

1002
01:09:07,970 --> 01:09:09,910
If you're going to call, at least say something.

1003
01:09:10,440 --> 01:09:11,540
Who is this?

1004
01:09:12,280 --> 01:09:13,509
Who are you, you punk?

1005
01:09:13,510 --> 01:09:16,150
This little brat. Who are you, making a prank call?

1006
01:09:16,350 --> 01:09:17,650
Who are you, you punk?

1007
01:09:20,050 --> 01:09:21,090
Unbelievable.

1008
01:09:23,420 --> 01:09:26,359
Anyway, people like this should all be rounded up and jailed.

1009
01:09:26,360 --> 01:09:27,390
These little punks.

1010
01:09:28,490 --> 01:09:30,260
The laws in this country are way too lenient.

1011
01:09:48,050 --> 01:09:49,150
Hello?

1012
01:09:49,350 --> 01:09:50,350
Hey.

1013
01:09:51,480 --> 01:09:52,850
It's me, Seo Jong Hee.

1014
01:09:54,220 --> 01:09:55,220
Hey.

1015
01:09:55,990 --> 01:09:56,990
What?

1016
01:09:57,290 --> 01:09:59,890
I'm at a payphone, and I'm down to my last dime.

1017
01:10:00,190 --> 01:10:01,960
I'll make this quick, so listen up.

1018
01:10:03,290 --> 01:10:04,300
Okay.

1019
01:10:04,400 --> 01:10:06,260
Meet me in front of Vivaldi on Sunday at 1pm.

1020
01:10:06,860 --> 01:10:08,700
There's something I need to tell you in person first.

1021
01:10:11,400 --> 01:10:13,940
No, it's not something I can say over the phone.

1022
01:10:16,310 --> 01:10:17,310
Right.

1023
01:10:18,310 --> 01:10:20,980
It was bound to end up like this anyway.

1024
01:10:23,110 --> 01:10:24,880
More than my three fated encounters with him,

1025
01:10:25,180 --> 01:10:30,090
their one encounter was a stronger and more powerful destiny.

1026
01:10:34,230 --> 01:10:35,290
So...

1027
01:10:36,060 --> 01:10:39,630
I'm taking back my claim to happiness.

1028
01:10:40,600 --> 01:10:41,630
Because...

1029
01:10:49,570 --> 01:10:53,850
You also have the right to pursue your own happiness.

1030
01:10:55,280 --> 01:10:56,350
And...

1031
01:10:57,420 --> 01:11:01,520
The person I want to be happy, second only to myself,

1032
01:11:05,520 --> 01:11:07,830
is you.

1033
01:11:31,550 --> 01:11:32,550
Yes.

1034
01:11:47,170 --> 01:11:48,330
That's nice.

1035
01:11:48,730 --> 01:11:50,229
But why the pumpkin porridge all of a sudden?

1036
01:11:50,230 --> 01:11:52,599
The tutor's younger siblings brought it over.

1037
01:11:52,600 --> 01:11:53,770
- His siblings? - Yes.

1038
01:11:53,970 --> 01:11:56,709
His little brother is around Sae Ri's age,

1039
01:11:56,710 --> 01:11:58,940
and his sister is a couple of years younger.

1040
01:11:59,140 --> 01:12:01,379
I guess the tutor is the eldest son.

1041
01:12:01,380 --> 01:12:03,179
Their father passed away young...

1042
01:12:03,180 --> 01:12:05,079
There's no need to be...

1043
01:12:05,080 --> 01:12:07,590
so nosy about other people's family business.

1044
01:12:08,620 --> 01:12:09,719
He's not a stranger.

1045
01:12:09,720 --> 01:12:11,019
- Sae Ri, come on. - Yes, Sae Ri.

1046
01:12:11,020 --> 01:12:12,190
- Have a seat. - Come sit here.

1047
01:12:13,760 --> 01:12:14,959
- Eat your porridge. - That's a good girl.

1048
01:12:14,960 --> 01:12:16,129
- It's hot, so make sure... - Eat up.

1049
01:12:16,130 --> 01:12:17,130
You blow on it before you eat.

1050
01:12:17,131 --> 01:12:18,330
- Okay. - Okay.

1051
01:12:24,600 --> 01:12:25,600
Is it good?

1052
01:12:26,540 --> 01:12:28,140
- Mom. - Yes?

1053
01:12:28,670 --> 01:12:30,540
Where's my Cinderella pumpkin?

1054
01:12:31,140 --> 01:12:33,610
I put it over there, but it's gone now.

1055
01:12:34,350 --> 01:12:35,780
I wanted to keep it in my room.

1056
01:12:35,880 --> 01:12:36,909
That one?

1057
01:12:36,910 --> 01:12:38,820
Mommy made it into porridge.

1058
01:12:39,480 --> 01:12:41,150
You just ate it, Sae Ri.

1059
01:12:44,020 --> 01:12:45,720
- Can I have another bowl? - Sure.

1060
01:12:51,430 --> 01:12:53,059
My Cinderella pumpkin!

1061
01:12:53,060 --> 01:12:54,999
- Why did you eat it? - I'm leaving now.

1062
01:12:55,000 --> 01:12:56,669
I was supposed to make a carriage!

1063
01:12:56,670 --> 01:12:58,339
- Have some porridge before you go. - I hate you, Mom!

1064
01:12:58,340 --> 01:13:00,140
It's Saturday, so you have no lunchbox.

1065
01:13:00,400 --> 01:13:01,669
No, I'm fine.

1066
01:13:01,670 --> 01:13:04,010
- I'm leaving now. - My Cinderella pumpkin!

1067
01:13:10,380 --> 01:13:11,850
Are you back from your route already?

1068
01:13:12,050 --> 01:13:13,350
You're quick today.

1069
01:13:13,550 --> 01:13:16,950
Yes, it was pretty quiet out there because it's Saturday.

1070
01:13:24,860 --> 01:13:25,860
Why?

1071
01:13:26,360 --> 01:13:27,370
Just because.

1072
01:13:28,000 --> 01:13:29,030
You're so pretty.

1073
01:13:30,430 --> 01:13:31,440
Of course.

1074
01:13:31,640 --> 01:13:33,770
I'm one of the prettiest faces here at Cheongah Bus.

1075
01:13:36,170 --> 01:13:37,510
You really are.

1076
01:13:38,240 --> 01:13:39,510
Even now.

1077
01:13:44,350 --> 01:13:45,820
Right.

1078
01:13:46,680 --> 01:13:49,320
You're going to tell him tomorrow, right?

1079
01:13:50,020 --> 01:13:51,060
I have to.

1080
